news.title: Gurugram civic body sees 66% jump in stamp duty earnings in Apr-Aug 2022
news.para: The civic body has earned Rs 123 crore from stamp duty between April 1 and August 31 - a large hike from the Rs 74.3 crore collected in these five months in 2021.

news.title: Co-working operators leasing space at malls, hotels
news.para: "After finishing work, people look for a place to hang with friends. By operating a centre in a mall, there is no parking hassle, employees can go to the gym after work or to an eating place. For these reasons, co-working centres at malls are popular," said Amit Ramani, Founder & CEO, Awfis.

news.title: Noida: Post-demolition survey of Supertech twin towers done, report in a week
news.para: A team from Geo Structurals, an engineering company brought in by the demolition firm Edifice Engineering, carried out the survey from August 31 and completed it on Friday.

news.title: Noida: On twin towers land, Supertech wants another housing project
news.para: Emphasising that Supertech has ownership rights of the plot, and that the Noida Authority had allotted it for group housing, Arora said he will seek approval for a new project once the debris of the twin towers is cleared.

news.title: Reverse order that allows Mahira Group to collect money: Buyers to DTCP
news.para: During the meeting, STP Narendra Solanki assured buyers he would raise the matter with higher authorities. He, however, said he has to comply with the order issued by the headquarters.

news.title: Virat Kohli, Anushka Sharma buy eight-acre land in Alibaug to build farmhouse
news.para: The couple has paid stamp duty worth Rs 1.15 core for the conclusion of the deal that was registered on Thursday, showed the documents accessed by ET. The deal was documented on August 30, while final deal registration took place on Thursday.

news.title: Morgan Stanley Asia buys ACC shares worth Rs 215 crore
news.para: ​According to bulk deal data available with the National Stock Exchange (NSE), Morgan Stanley Asia (Singapore) Pte purchased 9,41,557 shares of the company.

news.title: Indore development body to give 2.64 hectares land for metro station
news.para: IDA chairman Jaypal Singh Chawda, collector Manish Singh, IMC Commissioner Pratibha Pal, CEO Ramprakash Ahirwar and T&CP joint director SK Mudgal on Thursday held a discussion over the agendas tabled in the board of directors’ meeting.

news.title: Odisha: NGT imposes fine of Rs 36 crore for illegal extraction of sand
news.para: The NGT's East Zone bench on Wednesday said given that illegal mining to the extent of over 1.49 lakh cubic metres of excess sand has been established at Mahupura, Dingiria and Arapata, Rs 36 crore has been imposed as total compensation to be levied for damage of the environment due to excess mining and illegal operation of the quarry without valid consent to operate.

news.title: Shyam Steel plans to invest Rs 2,500 crore to expand its production capacity
news.para: Shyam Steel reported a turnover of Rs 4,500 crore in the last fiscal year and will be looking to double it to Rs 9,000 crore in the next three years' time.

news.title: Haryana RERA threatens action against real estate agents for charging arbitrary brokerage
news.para: The real estate regulatory authority’s warning comes in the wake of number of complaints filed on daily basis in the city where the cheated buyers or allottees turn up for relief.

news.title: Punjab government to identify new quarries on private lands
news.para: The scrutiny or on-site inspection of the location which was shown as probable new quarries in the applications will be conducted by the sub-divisional level committee, the minister said.

news.title: Raze properties built on stormwater drains: Karnataka CM to BBMP
news.para: The CM personally inspected areas in Mahadevapura which witnessed severe flooding on Tuesday following heavy rain. He inspected the area near DNA apartment and Columbia hospital, Shantiniketan Layout, Ecospace and Sakra World hospital drain.

news.title: Not a single taker for Ahmedabad civic body rooftop solar panel rebate
news.para: Till date, just 50 citizens have applied for the rebate scheme and none of these applications have been cleared by the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC). The scheme was only open to bungalows, row houses and duplexes.

news.title: Ludhiana: Builders fume over rise in rates of construction material
news.para: According to the businessmen, the rates of white sand, steel, cement and all other material used in construction have increased by such extent that the cost of construction has risen manifold.
